    <note>Gu(3) Hui [23975] See documentation in 1148 jinshi list, wujia #96, for great grandson, Huan [11439]. Fujian TZ, 147.32b. He was also the 6th generation ancestor of Rulu [26038] (q.v.), which would make his elder brother, Fu [26039], the great grandfather rather than grandfather of the Gu(3) jinshi who use radical 75 (wood) as a generational indicator in their mingzi, which is logical since radical 85 (water) was the previous generational indicator. According to Liu Kezhuang, in his funerary inscription for Rulu, the Gu(3) were especially distinguished (youzhu) among the old lineages (jiuzu) of Putian.</note>
